      script: "Most sellers in Florida don't know this, but there's one day of the week that gives you a secret advantage the moment your house hits the MLS. It's Thursday. List on a Thursday and the MLS treats your home as \"new\" for two full weeks. Buyers see that \"new listing\" tag and they get excited. They move faster. They compete. And right now in Florida, priced-right homes are still pulling multiple offers. I'm talking 6, 7, 8 offers on the same house. But here's the truth nobody wants to say out loud. If you're sitting on the market with zero offers, it's not your agent, it's not your photos, it's your price. Buyers in 2024 have done their homework before they ever walk through your door. They are not overpaying. So before you list, drop your price range and your zip code below and I'll tell you exactly what homes near you are actually selling for right now.",
      caption: "Do you know the best day of the week to list your house on the MLS in Dallas Fort Worth?  It’s Thursday.  You get that “new listing” boost, which creates just a little more excitement for buyers scrolling… and that can turn into more showings right out of the gate.  And right now, the homes getting multiple offers? They’re doing a few things really well:  They’re priced right. They pull buyers in online. And they show REALLY well in person.  That combo is what gets buyers competitive.  If your home is sitting… I know you don’t want to hear this… but it’s the price.  Even if the comps say otherwise.  Buyers today have too much information. They’re checking everything… Google, TikTok, Realtor, AI… all of it.  If the price and perceived value don’t line up… they just move on.  So if you want it sold, you’ve got to be competitive. Otherwise… you might be living in it a little longer than planned.  DM me if you’re house hunting in DFW. #CourtneyBensonGroup #DallasRealEstate #collincountyrealestate #movingtotexas #cancerdallas",
      postDate: "2026-04-02",
